The '''International Maritime University of Panama''' (in [[Spanish language|Spanish]]: '''Universidad Marítima Internacional de Panamá''', '''UMIP''') is a [[maritime college]] in [[Panama City]], [[Panama]]. It trains cadets to become [[merchant marine]] ships' officers. It is located in the [[Albrook (area)|Albrook]] area of Panama City, on the site of the former [[Albrook Air Force Base]].
Its main building (Building 810 in Albrook) was severely damaged by a fire in January 2008, although there were no injuries or fatalities. The fire is believed to have started in a storage area on the building's top floor.<ref> {{cite news | first = Wilfredo | last = Jordán Serrano | authorlink = | coauthors = | title = Industria marítima – Pese a incendio, Umip dará clases | url = http://www.prensa.com/HOY/negocios/1236135.html | archive-url = https://archive.is/20130131202109/http://www.prensa.com/HOY/negocios/1236135.html | dead-url = yes | archive-date = 2013-01-31 | work = | publisher = La Prensa | location = Panamá | id = | pages = | page = | date = 2008-01-15 | accessdate = 2008-01-21 | language = Spanish | quote = Como resultado del incendio en el ático, el edificio 810 quedó inutilizable porque se le quemó el techo. }} </ref> <ref>{{cite news |first=Lisbeth |last=Cortés |authorlink= |coauthors= |title=Siniestros: se quemo el ultimo piso - UMIP en llamas |url=http://www.critica.com.pa/archivo/01122008/suc08.html |work= |publisher=Crítica |location=Panamá |id= |pages= |page= |date=2008-01-12 |accessdate=2008-01-21 |language=Spanish |quote= |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080408065848/http://www.critica.com.pa/archivo/01122008/suc08.html |dead-url=yes |archivedate=2008-04-08 |df= }}</ref>
UMIP was established by a law passed in 2005, and it absorbed the former [[Escuela Náutica de Panamá]], which was founded in 1958.
The university's rector (president) is Aladar Rodríguez Díaz.{{cn|date=December 2017}}
