'''SuperProfs''' is an education technology startup founded in 2010 and based out of Bengaluru.<ref name=":0">{{cite book|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/connecting-students-with-professors-virtually-115012600009_1.html|title=Connecting Students with Teachers Virtually|publisher=Business Standard}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Why EdTech startups will be the next to top the Class|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tech/tech-news/Why-edtech-startups-will-be-the-next-to-top-the-class/articleshow/48384931.cms|publisher=The Times of India}}</ref> It provides exam preparation classes.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/education/college-and-university/entrance-preparation-at-your-convenience/article8114201.ece|title=Entrance preparation at your convenience|date=2016-01-17|newspaper=The Hindu|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X|access-date=2016-03-31}}</ref><ref name=":1" />

== History ==
SuperProfs was founded by Piyush Agrawal, a [[Stanford University]] PhD dropout, in 2010 to provide competitive exam preparation for Indian students.<ref name=":1">{{cite news|last1=Agrawal|first1=Piyush|title=I gave up my Stanford degree to start this company|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tech/tech-news/I-gave-up-a-Stanford-degree-to-begin-my-startup-in-India/articleshow/50220351.cms|publisher=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Cloud Based Education Technology Company|url=http://forbesindia.com/article/checkin/aurus-networks-cloudbased-online-courses/36347/1|publisher=Forbes India}}</ref> Piyush was named one of India’s top innovators under 35 in the EmTech Awards in 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=India's top Innovators under 35|url=http://www.livemint.com/Consumer/I2NPKHkEiYYDVVr2bQu1WP/Indias-Top-Innovators-under-35.html|publisher=Livemint}}</ref> He has also been featured in the Young Turks feature program of [[CNBC TV18]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Young Turks - India Edition|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_mupsUyq5qI|publisher=CNBC TV18}}</ref>

== Mobile app ==
SuperProfs success has in part been the result of a mobile app that works at slower speeds of Internet connection by allowing students to download lectures.<ref>{{cite book|title=Mobile App helps UPSC aspirants in Exam preparation|publisher=Business Standard|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/superprofs-launches-mobile-app-for-upsc-aspirants-115120100880_1.html}}</ref>  The download option bridges a technological gap in India.<ref>{{cite book|title=SuperProfs Mobile App launch|publisher=Business Standard|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/superprofs-com-launches-mobile-app-for-exam-preparation-115060300959_1.html}}</ref>

== Funding ==
SuperProfs has raised three million dollars from venture capital firms Kalaari Capital and IDG Ventures India in 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=Aurus Network raises $3 million|url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2014-12-29/news/57495064_1_kalaari-capital-aurus-network-idg-ventures|publisher=The Economic Times}}</ref>

